The Telegraph - Calcutta

 $500m to be spent

Port-of-Spain: Around $500 million would be injected the Caribbean economy for the cricket World Cup to be staged in the region in 2007. 

Michael Hall, general manager of the Jamaica Cricket 2007 Ltd, said $157 million would come from activities related to cricket while the rest will come from private sector. 

?Between $150 million to 200 million will be invested in renovation and in building of stadia facilities.? (PTI) 

